Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Perl >= 5.8 with the following (recommended) module versions:

* Config::Tiny/2.12           * BerkeleyDB/0.34
* WWW::Curl/4.05              * URI::Escape/3.29
* HTML::TokeParser/2.37       * Clipboard/0.09
* IO::Pager/0.05              * XML::Simple/2.18
* Term::ProgressBar/2.09

* Getopt::Long/2.35           * Pod::Usage/1.33
* File::Path/1.08             * File::Spec/3.12
* Digest::SHA/5.47            * POSIX/1.09
* Cwd/3.12                    * Encode/2.12

Note that the Clipboard module is OPTIONAL.


Installation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract:
    % tar xvjf clive-$release.tar.bz2 && cd clive-$release

Run:
    % ./clive [option]... [URL]...

Getting started:
    % ./clive --manual # See the EXAMPLES
    % pod2man clive > clive.1 # POD => *roff, see pod2man(1) documentation


Installation: FreeBSD (7.0)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From the ports:
  * devel/p5-Term-ProgressBar
  * databases/p5-BerkeleyDB
  * security/p5-Digest-SHA
  * textproc/p5-XML-Simple
  * devel/p5-Config-Tiny
  * www/p5-HTML-Parser
  * devel/p5-IO-Pager
  * net/p5-URI
  * ftp/curl
  -- Optional:
  * x11/p5-Clipboard

From CPAN:
  * WWW::Curl


Installation: Ubuntu (Hardy)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From apt: # Typically: "sudo apt-get install $module"
  * libterm-progressbar-perl
  * libcurl4-openssl-dev
  * libhtml-parser-perl
  * libconfig-tiny-perl
  * libberkeleydb-perl
  * libdigest-sha-perl
  * libxml-simple-perl
  * libfile-spec-perl
  * liburi-perl 
  * perl-doc
  -- Optional:
  * xclip (for Clipboard module below)

From CPAN: # Typically: "sudo cpan install $module"
  * WWW::Curl
  * IO::Pager
  -- Optional:
  * Clipboard
